description: OLIVER LAKE FEATURING FLUX QUARTET ~ RIGHT UP ON ~ 2017 Passin Thru Records 41236 http://i4.imageban.ru/out/2017/06/11/81cb6e0d3a80a3141cae796c361e9d28.jpg 1. HEY NOW HEY 06:47 2. 5 SISTERS 09:22 3. 2016 09:34 4. DISAMBIGUATE 07:04 5. RIGHT UP ON 09:06 6. SPONGE 06:55 7. EINSTEIN 100! 20:56 OLIVER LAKE: alto saxophone FLUX Quartet violin TOM CHIU violin CONRAD HARRIS viola MAX MANDEL cello FELIX FAN Oliver Lake features Flux Quartet performing seven of his original compositions for a string quartet. Lake himself performs on three of the pieces (Hey Now Hey, 5 Sisters and Disambiguate), creating an interesting discussion between saxophone and strings.The compositions are varied in approach, turning often to improvisation, thus offering unmatched eclecticism in a single album. Einstein 100!, the largest piece, has solo and duo sections highlighting the virtuosity of the FLUX quartet. - Passin' Thru
